text: Bingham County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. As of the 2020 census, 47,992 people lived there. The county seat and largest city is Blackfoot. == Communities == === Cities === * Aberdeen * Atomic City * Basalt * Blackfoot * Firth * Shelley === Census-designated places === * Fort Hall (part) * Groveland * Moreland * Riverside * Rockford === Unincorporated communities === * Finn * Pingree * Springfield * Sterling * Woodville == References == Category:1880s establishments in Idaho Territory Category:1885 establishments in the United States Category:Idaho counties
